<section id="about" class="section" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <div class="container-page max-w-5xl">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-12 md:gap-16">
      <div class="md:col-span-2">
        <h2 id="about-heading" class="display text-fore text-[clamp(2.25rem,5vw,4rem)] reveal">
          Hello,<br/>I'm <em>Daniel.</em>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-3 space-y-7 text-lg sm:text-xl leading-[1.7] text-sub">
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
          I'm a software engineer focused on the practical end of AI — the
          part where models meet messy data, real users, and uncomfortable
          deadlines. Most of my work sits between strategy and shipping:
          helping teams figure out <em class="text-fore not-italic">what</em> to build, then actually
          building it.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2">
          I work primarily in <strong class="text-fore font-medium">Python</strong>
          (FastAPI, FastMCP) and <strong class="text-fore font-medium">TypeScript</strong>
          (Next.js), with <strong class="text-fore font-medium">Supabase</strong>
          for data and auth. For agent work I build autonomous agents,
          multi-step workflows, and tool integrations that plug into the
          systems your team already uses.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-3">
          I care about systems that age well: clear interfaces, honest
          evaluations, sensible defaults, and code other people can read on a
          Monday morning.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
